            "DetailedDescription": "<h2><strong>Region Inverter</strong></h2>\n\n<p>\n  The Region Inverter vTool inverts a region, turning all areas outside the input region into the output region. This means that selected areas become unselected and unselected areas become selected.\n</p>\n<p>\n  The vTool provides several options for specifying the inversion mask size. This mask determines which part of the input region is inverted and subsequently output:\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Input Region:</strong> The inversion is applied to the entire input region. If a region doesn't have a size defined, the vTool outputs a region with an error.</li>\n  <li><strong>Custom:</strong> This allows you to manually specify the mask size using the <strong>Width</strong> and <strong>Height</strong> parameters.</li>\n  <li><strong>Auto:</strong> The inversion mask size is determined automatically. If the input region has a defined size, inversion is applied to the entire input region. If no size information is available, the inversion mask size specified by the <strong>Width</strong> and <strong>Height</strong> parameters is used.</li>\n</ul>\n</p>\n<h3>\n  <strong>Inputs</strong>\n</h3>\n<p>\n  <strong>Region:</strong> Accepts a region from all vTools that produce a region as an output, e.g., Thresholding vTools or Matching vTools.\n</p>\n\n<h3>\n  <strong>Outputs</strong>\n</h3>\n<p>\n  <strong>Region:</strong> Returns the inverted region.\n</p>\n\n<p><br></p>\n<h3>\n  <strong>Configuring the vTool</strong>\n</h3>\n<p>\n  Double-click the vTool to open a settings dialog. This is a graphical representation of the vTool's parameters.\n</p>\n<p>\n  You can also configure the vTool via the pylon API and the <strong>Features - All</strong> pane of the pylon Viewer.\n  All parameters listed there can be set via the pylon API. To study the effects of a parameter, change the parameter\n  values in the <strong>Features - All</strong> pane and watch the results in a pin data view when running the recipe.\n  For more details about parameters, select a parameter and check the <strong>Feature Documentation</strong> pane.\n</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>\n  <a href=\"8F9A26E8-8492-4D95-B916-1047BB3443ED\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"><u>Get help</u></a>\n</p>",
