            "DetailedDescription": "<!--\n  ~ //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  ~ //  Copyright (c) 2025 Basler AG\n  ~ //  Author: HN\n  ~ //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  -->\n\n<h2><strong>Histogram Statistics</strong></h2>\n\n<p>The Histogram Statistics vTool analyzes histogram data and outputs a number of statistical values. You can use the Histogram Extractor vTool to extract brightness values from an image and use those integer arrays as input.\n</p>\n\n<p>The vTool outputs the following statistical data:\n<ul>\n  <li>Minimum</li>\n  <li>Maximum</li>\n  <li>Mean</li>\n  <li>Median</li>\n  <li>StandardDeviation</li>\n  <li>PixelCount</li>\n</ul>\n</p>\n\n<p>\nIf you want to remove brightness values from the top and bottom of the distribution, e.g., because extremely high or low values may be caused by hot or dark pixels, you can do this via the following API parameters:\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Bottom Percentile:</strong> This allows you to specify which percentage of brightness values you want to remove from the bottom of the distribution. The default is 0.02, which means that values smaller than 2 percent of all values are removed.</li>\n  <li><strong>Top Percentile:</strong> This allows you to specify which percentage of brightness values you want to remove from the top of the distribution. The default is 0.02, which means that values higher than 98 percent of all values are removed.</li>\n  <li><strong>Discard:</strong> Enable this parameter to remove the top and bottom percentiles from the distribution before evaluation.</li>\n</ul>\n</p>\n\n<p><br></p>\n<h3>\n    <strong>Inputs</strong>\n</h3>\n<p>\n    <strong>HistogramData:</strong> Accepts integer arrays from the Histogram Extractor vTool. \n</p>\n\n<p><br></p>\n<h3>\n    <strong>Outputs</strong>\n</h3>\n<p>\n    <strong>Minimum:</strong> Returns the lowest index position of the input array, i.e., brightness value, of the histogram.\n</p>\n<p>\n    <strong>Maximum:</strong> Returns the highest index position of the input array, i.e., brightness value, of the histogram.\n</p>\n<p>\n    <strong>Mean:</strong> Returns the mean value of the histogram.\n</p>\n<p>\n    <strong>Median:</strong> Returns the median value of the histogram.\n</p>\n<p>\n    <strong>StandardDeviation:</strong> Returns the standard deviation of the histogram.\n</p>\n<p>\n    <strong>PixelCount:</strong> Returns the overall number of pixels that contributed to the histogram.\n</p>\n\n\n<p><br></p>\n<h3>\n    <strong>Configuring the vTool</strong>\n</h3>\n<p>\n  Double-click the vTool to open a settings dialog. This is a graphical representation of the vTool's parameters.\n</p>\n<p>\n  You can also configure the vTool via the pylon API and the <strong>Features - All</strong> pane of the pylon Viewer.\n  All parameters listed there can be set via the pylon API. To study the effects of a parameter, change the parameter\n  values in the <strong>Features - All</strong> pane and watch the results in a pin data view when running the recipe.\n  For more details about parameters, select a parameter and check the <strong>Feature Documentation</strong> pane.\n</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>\n    <a href=\"pylonVToolHistogramStatistics\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"><u>Get help</u></a>\n</p>\n",
