            "DetailedDescription": "<h2><strong>Mini Script</strong></h2>\n<p>\n    The Mini Script vTool allows you to run JavaScript scripts. For details on how to create scripts, refer to the Mini Script Programmer's Guide. This is available in the sample code directory of pylon Data Processing (default location: <strong>C:/Program Files/Basler/pylon/Development/Samples/pylonDataProcessing</strong>). Configured scripts are saved in the recipe file.\n</p>\n\n<p>\nThere are two methods for loading a script in the vTool:\n<ul>\n    <li><strong>Loading from file:</strong> Use the <strong>Filename</strong> parameter to specify the path to your script file , e.g., <strong>C:/MiniScriptScripts/IntersectionPointLines.js</strong>. Then, execute the <strong>Configure</strong> command. You can find examples of Mini Script script files in the sample code directory of pylon Data Processing (default location: <strong>C:/Program Files/Basler/pylon/Development/Samples/pylonDataProcessing</strong>).</li>\n    <li><strong>Loading via Copy and Paste:</strong> Paste your script code into the input field of the <strong>Script Code Staged</strong> parameter. Then, execute the <strong>Configure</strong> command.</li>\n</ul>\n</p>\n\n<p><br></p>\n\n<h3><strong>Inputs</strong></h3>\n\n<p>\n    Inputs are defined by the code of your script.\n</p>\n\n<p><br></p>\n\n<h3><strong>Outputs</strong></h3>\n\n<p>\n    Outputs are defined by the code of your script.\n</p>\n\n<p><br></p>\n\n<h3>\n    <strong>Configuring the vTool</strong>\n</h3>\n\n<p>\n  Double-click the vTool to open a settings dialog. This is a graphical representation of the vTool's parameters.\n</p>\n<p>\n  You can also configure the vTool via the pylon API and the <strong>Features - All</strong> pane of the pylon Viewer.\n  All parameters listed there can be set via the pylon API. To study the effects of a parameter, change the parameter\n  values in the <strong>Features - All</strong> pane and watch the results in a pin data view when running the recipe.\n  For more details about parameters, select a parameter and check the <strong>Feature Documentation</strong> pane.\n</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>\n    <a href=\"4F6BC2A7-B011-492A-9295-9C996CC10F38\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"><u>Get help</u></a>\n</p>",
