            "DetailedDescription": "<!--\n  ~ //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  ~ //  Copyright (c) 2024 Basler AG\n  ~ //  Author: AG\n  ~ //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  -->\n\n<h2><strong>Painter</strong></h2>\n\n<p>\n    Draws geometric figures and text as overlays onto an image. The figures and text are defined by the incoming data.\n</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<h3>\n    <strong>Inputs</strong>\n</h3>\n<p>\n    <strong>Image:</strong> Accepts images directly from a Camera vTool or any other vTool that outputs images.\n</p>\n<p>\n    <strong>Data1-n:</strong> Multiple data pins that accept data to be painted onto the image.\n</p>\n\n<p><br></p>\n<h3>\n    <strong>Outputs</strong>\n</h3>\n<p>\n    <strong>Image:</strong> Returns the image with the additional content painted onto it.\n</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<h3>\n    <strong>Configuring the vTool</strong>\n</h3>\n<p>\n    Double-click the vTool to open a settings dialog. This is a graphical representation of the vTool's parameters.\n</p>\n<p>\n    You can also configure the vTool via the pylon API and the <strong>Features - All</strong> pane of the pylon Viewer.\n    All parameters listed there can be set via the pylon API. To study the effects of a parameter, change the parameter\n    values in the <strong>Features - All</strong> pane and watch the results in a pin data view when running the recipe.\n    For more details about parameters, select a parameter and check the <strong>Feature Documentation</strong> pane.\n</p>\n<p>\n    Hints:\n    <ul>\n        <li>Use the <strong>InputDataPinSelector</strong> parameter to select the Data pin to configure.</li>\n        <li>Use the <strong>PinDescription</strong> parameter to add metadata for a Data pin, making it easier to remember what is connected.</li>\n        <li>Check the <strong>Feature Documentation</strong> for <strong>TextFormat</strong> to see available options.</li>\n        <li>Use the <strong>Features - All</strong> pane to test settings while the recipe is running.</li>\n    </ul>\n</p>\n",
